[Patient] How much water should I drink daily to manage my heart failure?
[Healthcare Educator] Aim for 8-10 cups of water a day, but adjust based on your doctor's recommendations.
[Patient] Can I drink other beverages like tea or juice?
[Healthcare Educator] Limit caffeine and sugary drinks, opt for herbal tea or diluted juice instead.
[Patient] How can I track my fluid intake effectively?
[Healthcare Educator] Use a water bottle with measurements or a phone app to track your intake daily.
[Patient] What should I do if I notice sudden weight gain?
[Healthcare Educator] Contact your healthcare provider immediately if you experience sudden weight gain or swelling.
[Patient] Are there any foods I should avoid to manage my fluid intake?
[Healthcare Educator] Limit high-sodium foods like processed snacks, canned soups, and fast food to help manage fluids.